Quote:  [Against the over use of bugger, bloody and hell] ... One of [these], the word b-y, is simply coarse and nasty, but it may have had a perfectly harmless, even pious, origin. ... Its absurd uses now ... `That's a high building, Tom.' ... `Not so bloody high.'
